message.content: One of the most significant events in the Federated States of Micronesia in the past 100 years is its political transformation from a United Nations Trust Territory to an independent nation. After World War II, Micronesia was administered by the United States under a UN trust until 1986 when it became a sovereign nation. This event, known as the Compact of Free Association, established the Federated States of Micronesia as a self-governing nation with its own constitution, government, and international relations. It marked a crucial milestone in the country's history, granting it sovereignty and the ability to shape its own future.
